				<h2>What is Diabetes?</h2>
				
				
				<p>Diabetes is a metabolic disease that leads to high blood sugar levels. Usually, insulin moves sugar from the blood to your cells, which can later be used in energy. However, people with diabetes can't make enough insulin or can't use the body's insulin. Severe diabetes can damage your nerves, eyes, kidney, and other organs. </p>
